name: Pikachu
description: Pikachu that can generate powerful electricity have cheek sacs that are extra soft and super stretchy.

name: Charizard
description: It spits fire that is hot enough to melt boulders. It may cause forest fires by blowing flames.

name: Bulbasaur
description: A strange seed was planted on its back at birth. The plant sprouts and grows with this POKéMON.

name: Squirtle
description: After birth, its back swells and hardens into a shell. Powerfully sprays foam from its mouth.

name: Caterpie
description: Its short feet are tipped with suction pads that enable it to tirelessly climb slopes and walls.

name: Weedle
description: Often found in forests, eating leaves. It has a sharp venomous stinger on its head.

name: Pidgey
description: A common sight in forests and woods. It flaps its wings at ground level to kick up blinding sand.

name: Rattata
description: Bites anything when it attacks. Small and very quick, it is a common sight in many places.

name: Spearow
description: Eats bugs in grassy areas. It has to flap its short wings at high speed to stay airborne.

name: Ekans
description: Moves silently and stealthily. Eats the eggs of birds, such as PIDGEY and SPEAROW, whole.

name: Quaxly
description: This Pokémon migrated to Paldea from distant lands long ago. The gel secreted by its feathers repels water and grime.

name: Tepig
description: It can deftly dodge its foe’s attacks while shooting fireballs from its nose. It roasts berries before it eats them.

name: Snorlax
description: Very lazy. Just eats and sleeps. As its rotund bulk builds, it becomes steadily more slothful.

name: Paldean Wooper
description: This Pokémon lives in cold water. It will leave the water to search for food when it gets cold outside.

name: Eevee
description: Its ability to evolve into many forms allows it to adapt smoothly and perfectly to any environment.

name: Cleffa
description: According to local rumors, Cleffa are often seen in places where shooting stars have fallen.

name: Quaquaval
description: A single kick from a Quaquaval can send a truck rolling. This Pokémon uses its powerful legs to perform striking dances from far-off lands.

name: Smoliv
description: It protects itself from enemies by emitting oil from the fruit on its head. This oil is bitter and astringent enough to make someone flinch.

name: Koraidon
description: This seems to be the Winged King mentioned in an old expedition journal. It was said to have split the land with its bare fists.

name: Pawmot
description: This Pokémon normally is slow to react, but once it enters battle, it will strike down its enemies with lightning-fast movements.

name: Bulbasaur
description: This Pokémon normally is slow to react, but once it enters battle, it will strike down its enemies with lightning-fast movements.
